1
00:00:00,914 --> 00:00:02,615
It's so vile.

2
00:00:02,640 --> 00:00:04,709
He's a teacher, an adult.

3
00:00:04,733 --> 00:00:06,496
How could he do this?

4
00:00:06,520 --> 00:00:09,240
This is exactly why
Thai quit singing completely

5
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:11,870
even though he
used to love it so much.

6
00:00:12,920 --> 00:00:16,110
If it's really okay
like you say, then that's good.

7
00:00:17,568 --> 00:00:18,895
But if not...

8
00:00:18,920 --> 00:00:21,570
We are ready to
help you with everything.

9
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:26,348
If you want to take action,
I'm with you. Let's go all the way.

10
00:00:26,373 --> 00:00:27,400
Hmm.

11
00:00:27,720 --> 00:00:28,960
If we succeed,

12
00:00:29,727 --> 00:00:31,607
the victims will dare to speak up.

13
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:36,103
And people like Teacher Boon
will learn to be afraid.

14
00:00:37,298 --> 00:00:40,553
The room has changed.
And the tapes are gone.

15
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:43,855
Jeez, and we almost got caught.

16
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:45,806
That clip Thai made...

17
00:00:45,831 --> 00:00:49,711
It sparked a movement
against sexual abuse.

18
00:00:49,745 --> 00:00:53,456
It's become a huge
social media debate now.

19
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:55,735
The one who was
wrong is the teacher.

20
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:58,323
He has always been
the one in the wrong, not us.

21
00:01:00,965 --> 00:01:05,445
I've seen and felt the courage
from both you and Thai.

22
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:07,983
I'm happy for you.

23
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:21,300
- Get out!
- Get out!

24
00:01:21,658 --> 00:01:23,384
Get out of here!

25
00:01:23,409 --> 00:01:24,640
Go away!

26
00:01:24,665 --> 00:01:26,360
No one wants you here!

27
00:01:26,385 --> 00:01:28,383
- Go!
- Get out!

28
00:01:28,408 --> 00:01:30,040
Get out!

29
00:01:30,064 --> 00:01:31,520
- Get out!
- Get out!

30
00:01:31,544 --> 00:01:32,844
Call the police!

31
00:01:32,869 --> 00:01:33,920
Go away!

32
00:01:33,944 --> 00:01:35,944
- Get out!
- Get out!

33
00:01:37,772 --> 00:01:40,083
- Blood!
- Are you okay?

34
00:01:41,303 --> 00:01:43,040
- Go!
- Go away!

35
00:01:43,064 --> 00:01:47,436
- Get out!
- Get out!

36
00:01:47,461 --> 00:01:49,000
Hey, why are you doing this?

37
00:01:51,505 --> 00:01:53,280
Mindy! Mindy!

38
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:55,145
- Serves them right!
- Mindy!

39
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:52,360
Why did you wake up so early?

40
00:02:53,710 --> 00:02:56,440
It's not time to go
to the airport yet, is it?

41
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:59,707
I guess I'm just excited, Liu.

42
00:02:59,731 --> 00:03:01,933
I haven't been to
Chiang Mai in a long time.

43
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:04,220
Go back to sleep.

44
00:03:09,069 --> 00:03:10,069
Sleep tight.

45
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:19,996
Is there something worrying you?

46
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,515
You can tell me.

47
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:23,963
Not at all.

48
00:03:25,393 --> 00:03:26,684
Hmm...

49
00:03:27,221 --> 00:03:30,223
Then don't forget
to buy me some souvenirs.

50
00:03:30,814 --> 00:03:33,655
Hmm. What do you want?

51
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,610
Northern sausage
and Green chili dip?

52
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:39,290
Hmm... I want Khao Soi Tad.

53
00:03:40,114 --> 00:03:41,527
And pickled peach.

54
00:03:41,551 --> 00:03:43,203
I love pickled peach.

55
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:46,520
- Khao Soi Tad and pickled peach?
- Hmm.

56
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:48,676
Okay. Go to sleep.

57
00:03:57,993 --> 00:03:59,473
"I can't sleep tonight."

58
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,960
"I've got a strange feeling."

59
00:04:20,373 --> 00:04:22,490
Horoscope for Pisces today.

60
00:04:22,978 --> 00:04:24,850
Love might not be so good.

61
00:04:25,379 --> 00:04:28,015
Beware of problems
in long-distance relationships.

62
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,775
Old relationships

63
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:32,760
or old flames might return.

64
00:04:35,188 --> 00:04:36,500
Oh no!

65
00:04:36,524 --> 00:04:38,587
What should I do?

66
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:41,703
This website is said
to be very accurate.

67
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:44,990
Long-distance relationships
will have problems?

68
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:49,055
Oh, no, no, no! I'm too old.

69
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,703
I don't want to start anything new.

70
00:04:51,473 --> 00:04:53,735
I heard you live
with your boyfriend.

71
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,840
How is that long-distance?

72
00:04:55,865 --> 00:04:58,175
Oh my... Editor Kong.

73
00:04:58,200 --> 00:05:00,120
My physical body is in Chiang Mai.

74
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:04,127
And Bangkok and Chiang Mai
are over 700 kilometers apart.

75
00:05:04,152 --> 00:05:08,129
Out of sight, out of mind.
Have you ever heard of that?

76
00:05:08,154 --> 00:05:10,307
Oh please.

77
00:05:10,331 --> 00:05:13,575
We flew here in the morning
and will be back in the evening.

78
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:16,400
What kind of drama
are you trying to stir up?

79
00:05:17,774 --> 00:05:19,262
Old flames...

80
00:05:19,286 --> 00:05:22,255
Just a little poke
and they reignite.

81
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:25,400
Jeez, maybe you should
focus on your work instead.

82
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,820
Didn't it say anything about that?

83
00:05:28,714 --> 00:05:30,480
Hmm. Eat up.

84
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:33,960
Come on.

85
00:05:37,816 --> 00:05:38,816
Mmm-hmm.

86
00:05:39,894 --> 00:05:41,560
This is so good.

87
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:43,280
How good?

88
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:44,916
This good.

89
00:05:52,590 --> 00:05:54,770
Hello? What's up, Ohn?

90
00:05:55,324 --> 00:05:57,830
You're in Chiang Mai already?
I was just about to call you.

91
00:05:58,880 --> 00:05:59,948
Is something wrong?

92
00:05:59,973 --> 00:06:02,530
No, I just wanted to tell you...

93
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:05,443
I'll be back a bit late tonight.

94
00:06:06,399 --> 00:06:08,022
Is there anything you want?

95
00:06:08,047 --> 00:06:10,055
Souvenirs or something?

96
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:12,895
No need to buy anything.

97
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:15,320
Besides, I'm all set.

98
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,280
Is that so?

99
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,040
Oh, right.

100
00:06:20,261 --> 00:06:22,823
We're out of cooking oil.

101
00:06:23,613 --> 00:06:27,575
And there's only one egg left.
I haven't gone to buy more yet.

102
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,600
And the laundry detergent...

103
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:32,086
- Can I have a coffee, Boy?
- Go ahead.

104
00:06:32,111 --> 00:06:34,397
- Who hasn't got one? / Thank you.
- Hello? Are you there?

105
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,400
How are you?

106
00:06:48,749 --> 00:06:51,742
Hello? Jee, are you listening?

107
00:06:51,742 --> 00:06:54,760
Hmm? I'm listening.

108
00:06:55,343 --> 00:06:57,880
Jee, is something wrong?

109
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,643
No, no. It's okay.

110
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:01,800
I've got to go.

111
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,440
Wait, wait... Jee!

112
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,240
How is everyone?

113
00:07:17,325 --> 00:07:18,690
You've gotten prettier.

114
00:07:18,715 --> 00:07:20,339
Thank you.

115
00:07:20,364 --> 00:07:21,709
Make yourselves comfortable.

116
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:22,992
Is work alright?

117
00:07:23,016 --> 00:07:24,255
Any problems?

118
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:26,120
Jee is here just in time.

119
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,563
Jira!

120
00:07:29,587 --> 00:07:31,495
Wow, still handsome as ever.

121
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:34,055
Here, I bought some coffee for you.

122
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:35,800
Do you still like hot Americano?

123
00:07:35,825 --> 00:07:37,143
Come take one.

124
00:07:50,859 --> 00:07:52,419
He didn't answer my questions.

125
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:56,400
And just hung up on me like that?

126
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,120
So cold.

127
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:06,640
Just break up with him already!

128
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:09,401
We're here to work,
ladies and gentlemen.

129
00:08:09,426 --> 00:08:11,495
Please pull yourself together.

130
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:12,753
Stop being paranoid for a sec.

131
00:08:13,905 --> 00:08:15,118
Sorry.

132
00:08:16,053 --> 00:08:17,173
Editor Kong,

133
00:08:18,055 --> 00:08:21,695
- about the writing I submitted...
- Let's worry about right now.

134
00:08:22,569 --> 00:08:25,703
Let's deal with this first.
Your writing piece can wait.

135
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:32,020
Oh, you're here.

136
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,840
From the publishing house, right?

137
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:36,384
- Yes. Hello, Mr. Bancha.
- Hello.

138
00:08:36,409 --> 00:08:40,320
- I'm Kong. We spoke on the phone.
- Yes, yes.

139
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:43,240
And this is Editor Mindy.

140
00:08:45,298 --> 00:08:47,975
And this is
our cartoonist, Mr. Ohn.

141
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,560
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

142
00:08:50,808 --> 00:08:52,560
Please come in and
make yourselves at home.

143
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:54,160
- Sure. Thank you.
- Yes.

144
00:08:56,152 --> 00:08:57,680
- Come in.
- Thank you.

145
00:09:01,402 --> 00:09:02,520
Make yourselves at home.

146
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:05,960
Take your time.

147
00:09:09,073 --> 00:09:10,660
When are you
planning to hold the event?

148
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:13,440
I think we've
discussed this, but I forgot.

149
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:17,060
Old folks are forgetful.

150
00:09:17,767 --> 00:09:19,935
It's in June.

151
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:22,400
It coincides with Pride Month.

152
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:24,120
Perfect timing.

153
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:26,187
Oh, right.

154
00:09:26,212 --> 00:09:30,360
Regarding the venue rental fee...

155
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,480
It's as we discussed, right?

156
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:35,055
Exactly as discussed.

157
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:38,476
We'll handle lighting for you.

158
00:09:39,125 --> 00:09:42,335
And if you want to
make any adjustments,

159
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:44,152
just let me know.

160
00:09:44,176 --> 00:09:45,976
I'll give you a special rate.

161
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:51,101
Wow, you're too kind.
This is already very generous.

162
00:09:51,126 --> 00:09:52,507
Hmm...

163
00:09:52,531 --> 00:09:54,531
Your gallery is huge,

164
00:09:54,556 --> 00:09:58,015
located right in the city center
and easy to get to.

165
00:09:58,040 --> 00:10:00,280
Why is the price...

166
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,200
So low?

167
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:06,360
Yes. The price is much
friendlier than other places.

168
00:10:07,476 --> 00:10:10,533
I consider it helping out.

169
00:10:11,008 --> 00:10:13,094
- Helping out?
- Yes.

170
00:10:13,901 --> 00:10:17,294
I want to support the third gender.

171
00:10:22,267 --> 00:10:24,106
Oh, I see.

172
00:10:25,294 --> 00:10:26,873
To add some diversity.

173
00:10:28,406 --> 00:10:30,406
Some people say my gallery...

174
00:10:30,916 --> 00:10:32,440
only exhibits boring work.

175
00:10:33,502 --> 00:10:35,166
Let them wait and see this event.

176
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:38,427
You can go ahead
and organize it to be

177
00:10:38,451 --> 00:10:41,506
flashy,
extravagant, and spectacular!

178
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:44,804
I want my gallery to be colorful.

179
00:10:44,828 --> 00:10:46,160
Go all out.

180
00:10:46,185 --> 00:10:48,339
Oh, thank you.

181
00:10:48,364 --> 00:10:49,760
Let's go!

182
00:10:50,964 --> 00:10:51,994
Wait for me!

183
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:59,016
- Kids having fun.
- Yes.

184
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:02,640
- They're my grandkids.
- Oh... I see.

185
00:11:09,798 --> 00:11:11,200
- Ready?
- Hmm.

186
00:11:12,298 --> 00:11:13,351
Action!

187
00:11:13,728 --> 00:11:15,600
Hello...

188
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:20,080
Welcome to
Georgie Sells Everything.

189
00:11:20,767 --> 00:11:23,640
What are we selling today, Georgie?

190
00:11:23,665 --> 00:11:24,942
Right here!

191
00:11:24,966 --> 00:11:27,832
Sandy, the Curry Bag Rubber Band!

192
00:11:27,857 --> 00:11:29,360
Let's zoom in for a better look.

193
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:32,560
What's more?
Even though it looks like this,

194
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:38,080
this is no ordinary rubber band.

195
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:40,400
It's made from bio-organic latex,

196
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:44,038
using state-of-the-art
engineering technology!

197
00:11:44,063 --> 00:11:49,319
Resulting in a toughness
of 9,999.99 millijoules!

198
00:11:49,344 --> 00:11:51,745
- Wow!
- Tougher than Grandma's skin!

199
00:11:51,770 --> 00:11:56,015
And strong enough to be used
to tie curry bags in space!

200
00:11:56,040 --> 00:12:00,520
With this, our Thai curry
can fly all the way to Mars.

201
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:02,560
Ouu...

202
00:12:02,843 --> 00:12:05,607
That's amazing!
How much is it?

203
00:12:05,632 --> 00:12:09,160
With these excellent features,

204
00:12:10,082 --> 00:12:11,230
You can have it for...

205
00:12:11,255 --> 00:12:12,390
only...

206
00:12:12,415 --> 00:12:13,415
One...

207
00:12:13,439 --> 00:12:14,976
One million baht.

208
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,880
- Only one million baht a piece!
- Ouu...

209
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:19,440
What?

210
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:22,800
Go right ahead.

211
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:25,280
I'm just here
to check out the venue.

212
00:12:27,766 --> 00:12:28,766
Hello.

213
00:12:29,147 --> 00:12:30,147
Hello.

214
00:12:31,296 --> 00:12:33,311
Next up, clay statues!

215
00:12:33,335 --> 00:12:35,016
Limited stock available.

216
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,280
- Yes!
- Yes!

217
00:12:36,305 --> 00:12:38,265
Don't miss it.

218
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:52,880
It's so pretty.

219
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,280
Yeah, really pretty.

220
00:12:54,280 --> 00:12:56,200
I have a lipstick. Want to try it?

221
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:58,840
- Let me see.
- I don't know what shade it is.

222
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,520
- Oh, this one?
- I think it suits you.

223
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:05,320
- So pretty.
- Very pretty.

224
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:07,280
What are you all doing?

225
00:13:10,406 --> 00:13:12,326
From now on, you're
not to play with Kit.

226
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:15,880
If I see any girl playing with him,

227
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:17,040
I will punish her.

228
00:13:17,533 --> 00:13:18,935
Do you understand, Duanpen?

229
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:20,240
Do you understand, Atchara?

230
00:13:22,143 --> 00:13:23,655
As for you, Kit...

231
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:25,480
Don't you like being a man?

232
00:13:26,245 --> 00:13:27,895
I'll have to fix your habits.

233
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:30,655
Go play football with boys.

234
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:33,175
Hey, why is Kit getting scolded?

235
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:36,655
How can a man act like this?
Look at what you're wearing.

236
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:38,043
It's because he's a sissy.

237
00:13:40,599 --> 00:13:43,159
Wipe it all off.
I said wipe it off!

238
00:13:47,323 --> 00:13:49,268
And look at this.
What are you wearing?

239
00:13:49,292 --> 00:13:50,936
Take it off.

240
00:14:00,248 --> 00:14:01,248
Ohn.

241
00:14:03,593 --> 00:14:04,993
I've never liked myself.

242
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:14,840
And I know that
no one likes me either.

243
00:14:19,941 --> 00:14:22,640
I don't like that
I was born this way.

244
00:14:30,087 --> 00:14:31,567
I wanted to be born a girl.

245
00:14:57,872 --> 00:14:59,560
- Nird.
- Yes?

246
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:01,440
Please give this to Kik.

247
00:15:01,465 --> 00:15:02,640
Okay.

248
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:16,560
Is this the legendary Boy?

249
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:19,080
The one they say quit
and became super successful?

250
00:15:19,104 --> 00:15:20,440
- Yeah.
- Wow.

251
00:15:20,464 --> 00:15:23,753
He left ages ago
and opened a shoe shop.

252
00:15:23,778 --> 00:15:25,760
- It's famous on IG.
- Let me see.

253
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:28,080
He's rich now. This is his IG.

254
00:15:29,130 --> 00:15:31,370
Wait, there's a promotion
for a Pride Collection too!

255
00:15:31,395 --> 00:15:32,560
I need to save up for this.

256
00:15:32,585 --> 00:15:36,815
Seriously?
That's total rainbow washing.

257
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,200
What is rainbow washing?

258
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:43,840
Rainbow washing is when
businesses use the LGBTQ+ community

259
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:46,000
as a marketing tool.

260
00:15:46,025 --> 00:15:50,118
In reality, they don't have
any policies to support equality.

261
00:15:50,118 --> 00:15:51,920
Simply put, it's fake.

262
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:55,655
Ouch! That's harsh.
Why are you dissing him?

263
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:57,680
The old employees all know

264
00:15:57,705 --> 00:16:01,195
that he's a super straight man,
borderline chauvinistic, you know?

265
00:16:01,220 --> 00:16:04,615
How so? I don't quite get it.

266
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:07,680
Saying this sounds like
I'm stereotyping all men.

267
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:12,055
But he represents
the epitome of a traditional man.

268
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:14,440
He's only a few years
