Kong. Ohn.

541
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:03,920
Before we go to the next gallery,
can we stop somewhere first?

542
00:33:04,480 --> 00:33:05,480
Whatever.

543
00:33:13,582 --> 00:33:14,582
- Get out!
- Get out!

544
00:33:14,607 --> 00:33:15,821
"Chiang Mai Buddhist Center"

545
00:33:15,846 --> 00:33:17,846
"Stop the transgender parade."

546
00:33:17,877 --> 00:33:21,412
- Get out!
- Get out!

547
00:33:25,893 --> 00:33:27,310
"Stop the Pride parade!"

548
00:33:31,258 --> 00:33:34,320
The Sao Saw Et incident
became the starting point

549
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:37,303
of the movement
for rights and freedom.

550
00:33:38,285 --> 00:33:41,368
So much so that
they designated February 21st

551
00:33:41,393 --> 00:33:43,953
as the day to end violence...

552
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:46,800
against gender-diverse people.

553
00:33:49,080 --> 00:33:52,960
It's similar to the beginning
of Pride Month, isn't it?

554
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:57,975
It started when
police began using violence

555
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:02,448
against a customer at
Stonewall Inn gay bar in New York.

556
00:34:02,473 --> 00:34:05,440
Until the situation
escalated into a riot.

557
00:34:06,280 --> 00:34:08,080
That's why they hold
commemoration events.

558
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:11,696
Events like this shouldn't
be buried and forgotten.

559
00:34:11,721 --> 00:34:14,200
They should be
remembered as a lesson.

560
00:34:16,040 --> 00:34:17,960
It's unbelievable
that something like this

561
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:20,156
could happen in our time.

562
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:24,782
Maybe aliens are laughing at us.

563
00:34:24,807 --> 00:34:26,828
Saying "Look at those earthlings."

564
00:34:26,853 --> 00:34:29,781
"What are they fighting about?
Why are they judging each other?"

565
00:34:29,806 --> 00:34:31,039
Exactly.

566
00:34:32,158 --> 00:34:34,400
I'm glad I came here with you guys.

567
00:34:35,552 --> 00:34:38,952
Is this the exact spot
where it all happened?

568
00:34:40,432 --> 00:34:41,438
Hmm.

569
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:44,695
It's sad when you think about it.

570
00:34:44,720 --> 00:34:48,720
Over 10 years have passed.
Has nothing gotten better?

571
00:34:50,160 --> 00:34:53,887
Actually, Mr. Bancha
has come a long way.

572
00:34:56,400 --> 00:35:01,135
You know what's really sad
about what he said?

573
00:35:01,160 --> 00:35:03,394
Some of us think like that too.

574
00:35:04,991 --> 00:35:06,655
During Sao Saw Et,

575
00:35:06,680 --> 00:35:09,280
those who came out
to oppose the Pride parade

576
00:35:09,280 --> 00:35:12,425
included LGBTQ+ groups too.

577
00:35:12,450 --> 00:35:16,575
They thought that gays and queers

578
00:35:16,600 --> 00:35:19,255
should be humble and stay quiet,

579
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:21,060
shouldn't come out
and demand rights

580
00:35:21,085 --> 00:35:24,015
bringing shame and
letting others look down on them.

581
00:35:24,040 --> 00:35:26,440
Wow, that hurts.

582
00:35:29,360 --> 00:35:32,255
It might be because of
the political situation then too.

583
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:34,640
It was very divided.

584
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:36,783
People were easily heated.

585
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:38,248
Really?

586
00:35:38,272 --> 00:35:40,295
I didn't know anything about that.

587
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:43,160
Kong, do you ever know anything?

588
00:35:44,133 --> 00:35:45,200
Oh please.

589
00:35:45,224 --> 00:35:48,975
I always care about
bread and butter issues.

590
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:51,495
I'm afraid of starving to death.

591
00:35:51,520 --> 00:35:54,680
That's the scariest thing.

592
00:35:56,387 --> 00:35:57,480
Oh, right!

593
00:35:59,996 --> 00:36:01,320
Editor Kong.

594
00:36:02,303 --> 00:36:04,320
About the writing I submitted...

595
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:05,920
Let's worry about right now.

596
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:09,680
Let's deal with this first.
Your writing piece can wait.

597
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:18,015
"If I ask about
the cartoon I submitted,"

598
00:36:18,040 --> 00:36:20,080
"will they get more stressed?"

599
00:36:20,647 --> 00:36:23,200
"Or will I be the one
who gets more stressed?"

600
00:36:23,894 --> 00:36:26,080
"It must have been bad."

601
00:36:26,680 --> 00:36:29,076
"Otherwise Mindy wouldn't
have hinted at it like that."

602
00:36:29,964 --> 00:36:33,560
"What should I do?
What should I do?"

603
00:36:39,400 --> 00:36:40,560
What's wrong, Ohn?

604
00:36:41,080 --> 00:36:42,080
Uh...

605
00:36:42,819 --> 00:36:44,275
I was going to ask something,

606
00:36:44,299 --> 00:36:45,396
but I forgot.

607
00:36:45,420 --> 00:36:47,592
- Huh?
- Never mind.

608
00:36:47,617 --> 00:36:48,817
Are you okay?

609
00:36:49,565 --> 00:36:50,578
Let's go.

610
00:36:51,183 --> 00:36:53,000
- I must be getting old.
- Exactly.

611
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:58,200
How do you feel

612
00:36:58,200 --> 00:37:02,120
about being crowned
the latest Miss Grand Milky Way?

613
00:37:02,120 --> 00:37:05,500
I'm so grateful to everyone

614
00:37:05,525 --> 00:37:07,966
who came to support me today.

615
00:37:07,991 --> 00:37:10,659
I want to say that I love you all.

616
00:37:10,684 --> 00:37:13,480
This crown and this stage prove

617
00:37:13,505 --> 00:37:14,791
that we have a place to stand.

618
00:37:14,816 --> 00:37:17,640
I hope we can ignite a fire
and create a new world together!

619
00:37:20,353 --> 00:37:21,827
- Hey.
- You look beautiful, Georgie.

620
00:37:21,852 --> 00:37:23,993
Isn't that Bancha's grandkid?

621
00:37:28,418 --> 00:37:29,980
You guys!

622
00:37:30,411 --> 00:37:33,040
Please don't tell my grandpa
that I'm practicing for the parade.

623
00:37:33,065 --> 00:37:34,878
For the Pride Parade?

624
00:37:34,903 --> 00:37:37,415
Yes. I want to join
the march with my friends.

625
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:40,003
But Grandpa won't let me.
He says it's dangerous.

626
00:37:40,028 --> 00:37:42,455
That people might
get angry and hurt us.

627
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:45,450
He's probably
just worried about you.

628
00:37:45,960 --> 00:37:48,290
Since you're all still kids.

629
00:37:48,315 --> 00:37:52,274
Tell you what,
we won't tell your grandpa.

630
00:37:52,299 --> 00:37:53,516
But I suggest

631
00:37:53,540 --> 00:37:55,996
you try asking for
his permission again.

632
00:37:56,713 --> 00:37:59,495
Besides, it's much safer nowadays.

633
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:01,200
Hmm, right.

634
00:38:01,560 --> 00:38:03,794
But you need to
take good care of yourselves.

635
00:38:03,819 --> 00:38:06,000
- Yes, thank you.
- Thank you.

636
00:38:08,953 --> 00:38:09,953
Let's go.

637
00:38:10,600 --> 00:38:11,640
How do I look?

638
00:38:12,367 --> 00:38:16,400
I don't know what these kids
have to face these days.

639
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:19,312
I just hope

640
00:38:19,336 --> 00:38:22,026
they don't have to go through
the same things we did.

641
00:38:23,520 --> 00:38:26,720
Problems change with time.

642
00:38:27,487 --> 00:38:30,759
They might not face
the exact same problems we did.

643
00:38:30,784 --> 00:38:34,520
But they will have to face
their own version of problems.

644
00:38:40,538 --> 00:38:41,638
Turn!

645
00:38:42,744 --> 00:38:44,520
- Am I pretty?
- Beautiful.

646
00:38:49,509 --> 00:38:50,509
Let's go.

647
00:38:58,357 --> 00:39:01,613
Then we pose?
Or should we spin?

648
00:39:01,637 --> 00:39:02,920
Let's spin.

649
00:39:03,360 --> 00:39:05,340
- Wave the flags?
- Yeah, wave the flags too.

650
00:39:30,826 --> 00:39:32,880
Two eggs.

651
00:39:33,528 --> 00:39:34,528
Check.

652
00:39:35,640 --> 00:39:37,080
Two, one.

653
00:39:37,771 --> 00:39:40,240
Another one...

654
00:39:41,591 --> 00:39:42,800
Food is served.

655
00:39:44,280 --> 00:39:45,400
Thank you.

656
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:53,615
See a handsome guy and
you can't help yourself, can you?

657
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:56,830
Acting all frisky, you fat sissy.

658
00:39:57,240 --> 00:39:58,370
What's the matter with you?

659
00:39:59,119 --> 00:40:00,923
Customer at that table.

660
00:40:00,948 --> 00:40:05,080
I saw you
making goo-goo eyes at him.

661
00:40:06,411 --> 00:40:08,158
I was just doing my job.

662
00:40:08,183 --> 00:40:10,924
Trans woman like you can't be trusted.

663
00:40:10,949 --> 00:40:14,880
But I think you should
go get chopped first.

664
00:40:14,905 --> 00:40:16,570
Consider it a friendly request.

665
00:40:16,595 --> 00:40:18,349
Just picturing it,

666
00:40:18,373 --> 00:40:20,241
too weird.

667
00:40:20,265 --> 00:40:21,616
A girl with a stick.

668
00:40:25,306 --> 00:40:26,440
Koy.

669
00:40:26,760 --> 00:40:28,560
You cannot speak to
your co-worker like that.

670
00:40:30,080 --> 00:40:32,299
Are we so slow that
you've got nothing to do,

671
00:40:32,986 --> 00:40:34,573
and have time
to stand here blabbering?

672
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:36,600
Get back to work.

673
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:38,160
Yes, Manager.

674
00:40:43,928 --> 00:40:48,175
Nam, if anyone speaks to you
like that again, let me know.

675
00:40:48,200 --> 00:40:49,410
I will take care of it.

676
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:51,935
How can you let them
talk to you like that?

677
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:53,679
You have to tell them off.

678
00:40:53,703 --> 00:40:54,886
Understand?

679
00:40:55,440 --> 00:40:56,960
Yes, thank you, Manager.

680
00:40:57,260 --> 00:40:58,640
Get back to work.

681
00:41:02,922 --> 00:41:03,922
Hmm.

682
00:41:07,424 --> 00:41:08,480
Yes.

683
00:41:22,600 --> 00:41:23,880
Ohn, what time is it?

684
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:28,200
We still have plenty of time.

685
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:33,480
In that case, let me go buy
some more gifts for Liu.

686
00:41:34,120 --> 00:41:36,200
Then I'll go find Editor Kong too.

687
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:38,240
He must be enjoying his shopping.

688
00:41:39,088 --> 00:41:41,728
Okay, I'll wait right here.

689
00:41:41,753 --> 00:41:42,753
Yeah.

690
00:41:43,360 --> 00:41:45,385
- Can you watch these?
- Mmm-hmm.

691
00:41:49,655 --> 00:41:52,280
"Missed calls (5)"
Oops, when did Jee call?

692
00:42:05,947 --> 00:42:07,240
Hello, Jee?

693
00:42:07,909 --> 00:42:09,047
Hello.

694
00:42:09,279 --> 00:42:11,440
- I just saw your call.
- Hmm.

695
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:15,390
Sorry about that.
I was busy looking for a gallery.

696
00:42:16,604 --> 00:42:19,080
We ditched the old one.

697
00:42:20,077 --> 00:42:21,430
We picked another one.

698
00:42:21,454 --> 00:42:23,970
It's more expensive,
but we feel much better about it.

699
00:42:25,053 --> 00:42:26,240
Are you okay?

700
00:42:28,880 --> 00:42:30,538
I'm fine.

701
00:42:30,960 --> 00:42:32,338
I just wanted to tell you...

702
00:42:32,362 --> 00:42:36,575
Do you remember Boy,
a guy I told you about?

703
00:42:38,954 --> 00:42:41,440
Boy?

704
00:42:41,642 --> 00:42:42,642
Oh...

705
00:42:43,579 --> 00:42:44,845
That guy,

706
00:42:44,869 --> 00:42:49,135
your ex-boss who stressed you out
so much you got gastritis?

707
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:50,160
Hmm.

708
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:52,826
- He came by the office today.
- What?

709
00:42:53,167 --> 00:42:54,359
What for?

710
00:42:54,384 --> 00:42:56,704
Don't tell me
he's coming back to work.

711
00:42:57,440 --> 00:43:01,240
No, he just came for a visit.

712
00:43:02,040 --> 00:43:03,520
Oh, good.

713
00:43:04,606 --> 00:43:06,006
So how are you? Are you okay?

714
00:43:07,640 --> 00:43:08,640
Well...

715
00:43:10,520 --> 00:43:12,480
He apologized.

716
00:43:13,033 --> 00:43:14,033
Apologized!

717
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:16,000
After all this time?

718
00:43:16,682 --> 00:43:19,360
Isn't it a little too late?

719
00:43:20,525 --> 00:43:22,080
Did he really mean it?

720
00:43:22,662 --> 00:43:23,862
Unbelievable, isn't it?

721
00:43:27,200 --> 00:43:29,840
Wait a minute.
Is it possible that...

722
00:43:31,800 --> 00:43:33,680
Horoscope for Pisces today.

723
00:43:34,440 --> 00:43:36,080
Love might not be so good.

724
00:43:36,720 --> 00:43:39,040
Beware of problems
in long-distance relationships.

725
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:42,640
Old flames might return.

726
00:43:44,680 --> 00:43:46,313
Is it possible that...

727
00:43:46,338 --> 00:43:50,460
He just realized
that he also likes men?

728
00:43:50,485 --> 00:43:53,960
And he's planning
to confess his love to you?

729
00:43:54,977 --> 00:43:57,010
Is this a plot for a new novel?

730
00:43:57,034 --> 00:43:58,626
It's so cheesy.

731
00:43:58,650 --> 00:44:01,385
Are you high on PM2.5?

732
00:44:01,868 --> 00:44:02,875
Hmm?

733
00:44:02,900 --> 00:44:04,276
Come on!

734
00:44:04,300 --> 00:44:07,793
Maybe the reason
he was so mean to you...

735
00:44:08,721 --> 00:44:14,040
was because he was trying
to hide his deep, deep desires.

736
00:44:14,763 --> 00:44:16,302
Actually...

737
00:44:16,692 --> 00:44:20,552
his heart has been
crying out for you all along.

738
00:44:21,689 --> 00:44:25,200
Thinking of you when awake,
dreaming of you when asleep.

739
00:44:25,225 --> 00:44:26,815
- Oh my...
- Everywhere he looks...

740
00:44:26,840 --> 00:44:30,600
- he sees your face everywhere.
- Oh my...

741
00:44:31,155 --> 00:44:33,907
Ew, I can't.

742
00:44:34,087 --> 00:44:35,680
No way.

743
00:44:36,238 --> 00:44:37,480
Are you sure?

744
00:44:37,840 --> 00:44:39,040
I'm sure.

745
00:44:40,980 --> 00:44:41,980
So...

746
00:44:42,799 --> 00:44:45,800
did you forgive him?

747
00:44:55,397 --> 00:44:56,990
You're not angry
at me anymore, right?

748
00:45:01,131 --> 00:45:02,760
I'm starting to realize
that this year...

749
00:45:03,553 --> 00:45:04,840
I'm getting older.

750
00:45:07,452 --> 00:45:09,120
Many friends around me...

751
00:45:10,334 --> 00:45:12,120
have fallen ill or died.

752
00:45:14,040 --> 00:45:16,396
Some from cancer,
some from heart disease.

753
00:45:19,732 --> 00:45:20,772
We...

754
00:45:22,240 --> 00:45:23,600
don't have much time.

755
00:45:26,115 --> 00:45:27,115
Jira,

756
00:45:28,178 --> 00:45:30,000
I want to clear my conscience too.

757
00:45:32,560 --> 00:45:34,796
For my own peace of mind
in my final years.

758
00:45:36,880 --> 00:45:38,130
All this time...

759
00:45:39,440 --> 00:45:41,550
I've wanted to apologize to you.

760
00:45:44,200 --> 00:45:46,069
And now I know that...

761
00:45:48,320 --> 00:45:50,129
a person can be anything...

762
00:45:52,320 --> 00:45:54,003
as long as they are talented...

763
00:45:55,280 --> 00:45:56,543
and a good person.

764
00:46:01,014 --> 00:46:03,975
I told you to fix it,
but it didn't get any better.

765
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:06,160
Do you understand
what "fix it" means?

766
00:46:06,160 --> 00:46:07,450
You're driving me crazy!

767
00:46:07,795 --> 00:46:10,096
I think you'd be
better off doing something else.

768
00:46:10,576 --> 00:46:14,240
Like designers,
makeup artists, or hairdressers.

769
00:46:14,240 --> 00:46:16,360
Those jobs would
suit people like you better.

770
00:46:17,560 --> 00:46:18,640
People like me?

771
00:46:19,280 --> 00:46:21,596
You know, the sissies and transgender.

772
00:46:22,280 --> 00:46:24,366
Aren't you supposed to
be good at that kind of stuff?

773
00:46:26,926 --> 00:46:29,080
"You know, the sissies and transgender."

774
00:46:41,720 --> 00:46:43,040
What's so funny?

775
00:46:47,421 --> 00:46:49,360
You don't understand
anything at all.

776
00:46:53,960 --> 00:46:56,600
You apologized just for yourself.

777
00:46:56,624 --> 00:46:57,986
That's all.

778
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:02,600
But I will forgive you.

779
00:47:05,880 --> 00:47:07,120
For myself as well.

780
00:47:11,333 --> 00:47:12,333
Thank you.

781
00:47:12,973 --> 00:47:15,800
In that case, can I...

782
00:47:16,770 --> 00:47:18,320
add you as a friend
on social media?

783
00:47:19,468 --> 00:47:22,240
Just so we can talk
or keep in touch.

784
00:47:25,139 --> 00:47:26,140
No.

785
00:47:29,015 --> 00:47:33,240
Just because I forgive you
doesn't mean we can be friends.

786
00:47:35,800 --> 00:47:37,333
You came to apologize...

787
00:47:38,400 --> 00:47:40,093
for your own peace of mind.

788
00:47:41,760 --> 00:47:43,326
And I forgive you.

789
00:47:44,600 --> 00:47:46,810
But I won't continue
this relationship.

790
00:47:48,880 --> 00:47:53,600
For my own peace of mind
in my final years too.

791
00:48:17,886 --> 00:48:22,137
You were amazing, Jee.
You did great. You're the best.

792
00:48:22,162 --> 00:48:26,963
I'll have to hold a reward ceremony
for you when I get back.

793
00:48:27,493 --> 00:48:30,672
I'll get you some
delicious Northern sausage.

794
00:48:30,697 --> 00:48:32,080
A really good one, okay?

795
00:48:32,104 --> 00:48:35,310
Get home safe. Good luck.

796
00:48:35,744 --> 00:48:36,960
Yeah. Bye bye, Jee.

797
00:49:12,867 --> 00:49:13,867
Hey,

798
00:49:14,040 --> 00:49:15,429
What have you been doing lately?

799
00:49:15,453 --> 00:49:18,073
Your skin looks so radiant.

800
00:49:19,640 --> 00:49:21,180
To be this beautiful,

801
00:49:21,204 --> 00:49:23,803
it's because I've collected
lots of karma points.

802
00:49:24,288 --> 00:49:25,546
Come on,

803
00:49:25,570 --> 00:49:27,691
Money makes you
beautiful in this life.

804
00:49:27,716 --> 00:49:29,915
Karma points makes you
beautiful in the next life.

805
00:49:29,940 --> 00:49:31,700
Are you secretly using some cream?

806
00:49:31,724 --> 00:49:33,616
Don't you lie and
lose your karma points!

807
